  "explanation": "Use a dynamic array for random access and a hash map to store indices for $O(1)$ insertion/deletion.",
  "answer": "class RandomizedSet:\n    def __init__(self): self.data, self.pos = [], {}\n    def insert(self, val):\n        if val in self.pos: return False\n        self.pos[val] = len(self.data); self.data.append(val); return True\n    def remove(self, val):\n        if val not in self.pos: return False\n        idx, last = self.pos[val], self.data[-1]\n        self.data[idx], self.pos[last] = last, idx\n        self.data.pop(); del self.pos[val]; return True\n    def getRandom(self): return random.choice(self.data)",
